To create a container image for Amazon ECS, you first need to create a Docker image of your application by writing a Dockerfile that describes the base image and the dependencies you want installed. Then, you can build the Docker image on your local system or Amazon EC2 instance and push it to Amazon ECR container registry for use in an Amazon ECS task definition. Finally, you can deploy this image by creating an Amazon ECS service that allows you to run and maintain multiple instances of your containerized application within an ECS cluster.

